This was good, the story was well though out and there were a few sustainable plot elements I could really believe. But, there were many bad ones as well. While there were 66 pages from cover to cover, I feels as if the story was rushed, focusing too much on the sex and not enough on the progression. Maybe a transfer of 3-5 pages would have fixed that, and done the rest of the doujin justice. The ending was very sudden, just expecting us to just calm down from a high that happened not even 8 pages earlier.

The line work and art was great, no complaints and only praises for the artists of this doujin.

Extra details, nothing much. If it was a few pages longer it would have boosted it greatly, and maybe if they tacked on just a bit more into the past of the girl and the father, there could have been more of a connection there, but like so many disappointing doujins, it just doesnt expand on anything, giving us face value items without much content.

Final rating? 8/10, I'd read it again
